cs.SY, cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a CPS management framework and analyses the dynamics of the IoT network in the cyber-space, which falls under the domain of systems and control. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the impact of emerging IoT protocols on the CPS infrastructure and proposes a diffusion model to analyse the propagation of interference in the IoT subsystem. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper addresses the issue of CPS safety and proposes a surveillance mechanism to trigger reconfiguration of the CPS when it is under stress. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed diffusion model can be considered as a form of AI-based analysis of the IoT subsystem. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The proposed CPS management framework uses a layered architecture for efficiency and scalability, which is a common approach in distributed computing.
